EUR 400 million for the construction of a new
The Hungarian finance minister, János Veres, and the vice-president of the European Investment Bank, Marta Gajecka, signed three agreements in Budapest on Friday for a credit line worth €400 million to support education, transport infrastructure, the environment and energy.
In 2006, the European Investment Bank (EIB) adopted a budget of EUR 300 million for the Hungarian budget financing of transport and environment projects to be implemented from the Cohesion Fund, for which a credit agreement worth EUR 100 million has already been signed by the parties.
The agreement on the EUR 150 million loan also covers the budgetary financing of education-related projects.
