The lawyer of the families of the victims Igor Veleba wants to get from the Třebíč hospital a compensation of 12 million crowns plus expenses.
Three million for each of the mothers, two million for the fathers and one million for each of the children.
The hospital is offering a maximum of $200,000 for each parent.
That is why the lawyer of the hospital Ondřej Dostál is absolutely not in agreement with Veleba's proposal.
"We reject such a claim, it is very, very high", Dostál said after the hearing.
"In order to be able to form an opinion on the counter-proposal, we need the expert report which the opposing party has commissioned.
Let's see if this one has any explanatory value.
But we continue to think that the total should not exceed hundreds of thousands", Dostál stressed.
The amount should, according to him, be set at between 100,000 and 200,000 CZK for each of the four parents.
At the beginning of the case, Jabloňov's family demanded one million crowns for each month they could not raise their biological daughter.
Veleba used the expert report, which was prepared for him by the University Hospital Centre in Prague-Motol, as a supporting document for the negotiations on the compensation.
According to psychological and psychiatric experts, the parents suffered psychological damage and were subject to stress of varying degrees and depth.
The stress was better tolerated by the men, although they were confronted with the remorse of not being able to prevent the substitution of newborns.
Women, on the other hand, are less calm about the experience of trauma in the news and about what is happening precisely at this time, summarized the content of the Veleba report.
Veronika and Nikola were replaced by nurses at the hospital in Třebíč on 9 December last year.
Last week, the children returned to their biological parents - Nikola to the Čermák family in Přibyslavice and Veronika to Libor Brož and Jaroslava Trojanová in Jabloňov.
At the end of October, the governor of the Vysočina region, Miloš Vystrčil, gave each of the families 100,000 krona to reimburse the expenses incurred by the mistake of the Třebíč hospital run by the region.
All hospitals in the Czech Republic are obliged by law to have civil liability insurance.
In case of failure, they must draw on the reserve fund, exceptionally, they can ask the manager for help.
Until now, the courts have awarded relatively small damages, the amounts calculated from the tables being in the hundreds of thousands, exceptionally in the millions.
Polívka has lost the Valašské Království (the Kingdom of Valašsko) which was the first to be established in the country.
Bolek Polívka has lost the case concerning the Valašské království (Kingdom of Valašsko) trade mark.
According to the judge of the regional court of Ostrava, it was indeed he who first used the title King of Valašsko, but the project was set up by the team around Tomáš Harabiš, the actor's former collaborator.
Polívka was not present at today's hearing.
But according to his lawyer, the case is probably not over and his client will appeal.
"The dispute is about Mr. Harabiš and his team parasitizing the popularity of Bolekív Polka", Polívka's lawyer said after the trial.
According to him, the words Kingdom of Valašsko remind everyone of this actor and comedian.
Harabiš agrees with me.
"We have almost ten years of work behind us.
"We are looking for money and events", he said.
He thinks money is the cause of the dispute.
"After years, they realized that the project was successful and that they could benefit from it.
They are the ones who want to parasitize our work", he added.
A profitable business
According to the court, it was Polívka who first used the title Valašský král (King of Valašsko) in his TV show.
The actor Radoslav Brzobohatý crowned him king in 1993.
But back then, it had nothing to do with the project of setting up a fictitious kingdom.
A few years later, Harabiš came up with the idea of issuing passports from the Valašské Království.
From a humorous action at the beginning, a business and a lucrative commercial activity emerged, followed by the creation, by Harabiš, of the Valašské království company.
In 1997 Polívka agreed to have her name and signature mentioned in the passport and even offered holders of the passport balances on the price of visits to her farm and theatrical performances.
Who's gonna sit on the throne?
Today, the judge also mentioned that Harabiš only used the nude idea, published by Polívka in the show manéž, for commercial purposes.
"The popularity of Boleslav Polívka certainly helped the Valašské království project", said the judge.
She added, however, that the heart of the project was Harabiš and his team who were devoted to the project in an intense way.
The collaboration between the now hostile parties continued until 2000 when Harabiš arranged for Polívka to be officially crowned in Vsetín.
But from then on, conflicts began to build up between Polívka and Harabiš, which culminated in the deposition of "King Boleslav I elected for ever".
The leading role in the kingdom was then, under the inspiration of Harabiš, assumed by the singer Jarmila Šuláková as Queen Mother.
Then, in 2002, Polívka filed a complaint against Harabiš and his company, a request that the court has today rejected.
What might help to solve the case is the tournament for the throne and half the princess.
A new king should come out.
He didn't want to give up the details and the date yet.
"We don't want to rush into things.
It would be something like the parade of kings in Slovácko.
The king would be elected for a certain time.
Even Mr Polívka can of course register", added Harabiš.
The Peugeot 207 SW 1.6 VTi test: the end of prejudice
I'll be honest, I was never a big fan of the Peugeot 206.
Its handling qualities were not extraordinary, the quality of the gear change, the driving and also that of the manufacture could, in many respects, be described as below average.
Now, however, its successor, the Peugeot 207, is on the market.
Especially since the SW-named combo is going one step further, I have to think about it.
When I was testing the classic hatchback Peugeot 207 I complained about the headroom in the back seats, for example.
So that's the end of the complaints because the combi bodywork means that even the big devils will be, in this respect, comfortable.
Let's see what we can do.
I will refer very quickly to the interior so that I do not repeat myself too much.
It's a pretty good design, my only comment about the central tunnel, which I think is poor.
Now, I would have liked a little more inventive design, given that the car looks so elegant.
The seats are comfortable and the days of complaining about chairs or too short a briefcase are over.
The lateral guidance has also been markedly improved over the 206 model.
As for the space, the increase in the dimensions of the bodywork is also noticeable there.
The combi also sees the lack of space above the head already mentioned disappear.
A safe in the safe
So the most important thing about this vehicle is its luggage compartment.
I must rate this one as very well accessible (also thanks to the rear swivel glass) and of a rather easy fitting.
