What exactly happened on Sunday?
As always in this type of event, official versions and rumors are opposed.
What were the circumstances of the accident?
According to the first elements of the investigation of the General Inspectorate of the National Police (IGPN), a police car was driving on Sunday, shortly after 5 pm, on Louise-Michel Street, in Villiers-le-Bel.
"It was not in intervention but in patrol, and was travelling at 40-50 km/h, without a gyrophare", explains a police source.
