What kind of insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver in the event of an accident, is a considerable expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, length of driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured, and use, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
The choice of the right car insurance is even more difficult than the choice of the vehicle model.
And it's that choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is embodied in an insurance contract, which states that the company receives the value of the premium awarded and in exchange becomes liable for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a loss.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is determined by various factors, such as age, sex, length of driving licence, marital status, type of vehicle to be insured or use of the vehicle, among others.
Insurance companies set their prices according to statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the odds.
For this reason, people over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower rate of claims due to their prudence.
Similarly, using surveys, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will influence the frequency and therefore the likelihood of an accident.
The higher the frequency, the higher the odds.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when setting the premium price.
This is why the driver must study the situation carefully to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
We will discuss the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it not only adapts to the insurer's characteristics but also offers a reasonable price.
Young people under 25 face various disadvantages when taking out insurance at an affordable price, such as low driving experience and a long-standing driving licence.
Although the ideal way to get a good insurance policy is to buy a life insurance policy that covers all risks, there are other, more economical options.
The more farsighted drivers can opt for all-risk insurance with a sense of openness, so that they can get the coverage of all-risk insurance at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays part of the amount of the claim.
"The part of the amount of the loss that the customer pays will be determined according to the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount", says Luis Noguera, the head of First Europa in Spain, an online insurance broker.
Another option is extended third party insurance, so that the customer has protection against damage caused to third parties, but not for damage caused to his own car.
In addition, it would be insured against theft, fire, and loss of the vehicle.
A word of advice.
If you are under 25 years old try to be cautious and avoid claims as much as possible, as this will affect the premium, which may reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the company's basic rate.
Instead, a penalty is an increase in the basic rate.
"The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its profits.
If the company has had a good year it can afford to increase bonuses", Noguera said.
After the age of 25 it becomes easier for drivers to sign an insurance contract, since the accident rate is reduced by the experience gained.
For this reason it is better to choose a full-risk insurance policy with a clear understanding of the risks involved.
"Normally young people cannot benefit from the experience acquired after an accident", says the director of the European company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur during the second year of driving, after the 'fear of the novice' has passed.
However, if the client is married but has no children yet, it is preferable to negotiate a comprehensive insurance, as long as his financial situation allows it.
Child marriages are considered by insurers to be the ones with the lowest claims rate, because the premiums will be lower.
In this case the best insurance would be a full risk insurance with a deductible (which could be 300 euros), or an extended third party insurance from the third year of the vehicle's life when the insured has a high level of premium.
"They have a more relaxed attitude and they have a greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of taking on a larger amount of franchisees", says Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, a full risk insurance with a deductible is preferable (they are 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the event of accidents, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is essential to study properly the insurance that is most suitable for us according to our personal situation.
