Everyone is hoping that the Federal Reserve will lower rates in the wake of the global stock market boom.
Stocks soared on both sides of the Atlantic yesterday after markets hoped the Federal Reserve would try to calm credit conditions, later cutting interest rates promoted by the central bank's vice president's soothing statements.
Stock markets are booming in London, New York and across Europe after Donald Kohn, second only to Ben Bernanke, chairman of the Federal Reserve, said that decision makers must be "flexible and pragmatic" in their actions in the turbulent financial markets.
