The Commission has also been asked to provide a report on the implementation of the new rules on the protection of the financial interests of the Union.
These comments are seen by investors as a clear signal that the Federal Reserve is ready to inject new capital into the US markets, and that further interest rate cuts could stabilise credit conditions.
